The testimony of Norma Mngoma, estranged wife of former minister Malusi Gigaba, has been moved to next week. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The State Capture Inquiry has postponed Norma Mngoma's testimony to Tuesday. Mngoma is the estranged wife of former cabinet minister Malusi Gigaba. WATCH: State Capture Inquiry resumes She was arrested last year for allegedly trashing a car, but charges were recently scrapped. She claims Gigaba doesn't want her to speak about his relationship with the Guptas.